line: Are you a semicolon? Because you complete me.
Are you an exception? Because I can't handle you.
You must be a loop, because you keep running through my mind.
Are you a function? Because I'd call you anytime.
Are you a variable? Because my love for you is always dynamic.
You had me at 'Hello World.'
My love for you is like an infinite loop - it never ends.
Are you a compiler? Because you turn my code into something beautiful.
You're the exception to my rule.
Are you a keyboard? Because you're just my type.
Are you Python? Because you make my life simpler.
Is your name Java? Because you keep me awake.
Are you JavaScript? Because you bring my world to life.
You must be HTML, because you structure my world perfectly.
Are you CSS? Because you make my life style better.
If they made you in C, you would have a pointer to my heart.
Are you a Swift protocol? Because you define my expectations.
You must be PHP, because you preprocess my heart.
Are you SQL? Because you SELECT my heart.
Are you a Go routine? Because you make my heart run concurrently.
Are you Git? Because you've merged perfectly with my heart.
I'm not sure if I should commit to you or just push you away.
Are you a repository? Because I can't commit without you.
Let's fork this relationship and see where it goes.
You're like a pull request - I want to merge with you.
Are you a version control system? Because I can't commit without you.
My heart just ran a successful 'love you' function.
You're the main branch to my repository.
Are you a debugger? Because you just fixed all my problems.
You must be a 404 error, because I've never found anyone like you.
Are you a syntax error? Because you stop my world.
I must be a bug, because I can't stop thinking about you.
You're the solution to all my compilation errors.
Are you a stack overflow? Because you've completely taken over my thoughts.
My code was broken until you came along.
Are you an array? Because you hold everything I need.
You must be a binary tree, because you make my heart search and sort.
Are you a hash map? Because you're the key to my heart.
You're like a perfectly optimized algorithm - efficient and beautiful.
Are you a linked list? Because I want to traverse through life with you.
You must be a queue, because I've been waiting for you.
Are you a stack? Because you're always on top of my mind.
Are you Wi-Fi? Because I'm feeling a strong connection.
You must be HTTP, because you're the request to my response.
Are you a API? Because I want to interface with you.
Is your name Google? Because you have everything I'm searching for.
You're like HTTPS - secure and always protecting my heart.
Are you a server? Because my heart responds to your ping.
You must be a firewall, because you're blocking everyone else out.
You're the primary key to my database.
Are you a JOIN statement? Because you complete my query.
You must be a foreign key, because you link to my heart.
Are you NULL? Because you complete me.
You're like a well-indexed table - fast and efficient.
Are you a database? Because I want to query you all night.
Are you a class? Because I want to instantiate you.
You're the object of my inheritance.
Are you polymorphism? Because you can be anything I need.
You must be encapsulation, because you hide your beauty so well.
Are you an interface? Because I want to implement everything about you.
You're like a singleton - there's only one of you.
Are you a microservice? Because you're perfectly designed.
You must be Docker, because you containerize my heart.
Are you cloud computing? Because you make everything scalable.
You're like CI/CD - you make everything smooth and automated.
Are you machine learning? Because you're training my heart to love you.
You must be blockchain, because our connection is immutable.
Do you believe in love at first byte?
You make my software turn into hardware.
You're hotter than my laptop's CPU.
Are you a password? Because you're exactly what I've been looking for.
You must be root access, because you have complete control over my system.
Are you a cache? Because you speed up everything in my life.
You're like a well-commented code - beautiful and easy to understand.
